    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSince version 0.12.0, LSP omni completion in C++ code with clangd unexpectedly deletes `->` in some contexts.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bb862d24-6815-4a48-87f2-c16e0619c4e6\n\nI have bisected this bug and found the first bad commit to be 36db6ff2c128864840e2820491a2172d6b1b7e62 (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/37491)\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nMinimal init.lua:\n```lua\nvim.opt.completeopt = { \"menu\", \"popup\", \"longest\" } -- \"longest\" required for repro\n\nvim.lsp.config['clangd'] = {\n  cmd = { 'clangd' },\n  filetypes = { 'c', 'cpp', 'objc', 'objcpp', 'cuda' },\n  root_markers = {\n    '.clangd',\n    '.clang-tidy',\n    '.clang-format',\n    'compile_commands.json',\n    'compile_flags.txt',\n    'configure.ac', -- AutoTools\n    '.git',\n  },\n  capabilities = {\n    textDocument = {\n      completion = {\n        editsNearCursor = true, -- this option is required for repro\n      },\n    },\n    offsetEncoding = { 'utf-8', 'utf-16' },\n  },\n}\n\nvim.lsp.enable('clangd')\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspAttach', {\n  callback = function(ev)\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(ev.data.client_id)\n    if client:supports_method('textDocument/completion') then\n      vim.lsp.completion.enable(true, client.id, ev.buf, { autotrigger = false })\n    end\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nI found that `editsNearCursor = true` (as configured by [nvim-lspconfig](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/lsp/clangd.lua#L84)) is required to reproduce this bug.\n\nThis bug only seems to occur when `completeopt` contains `longest`\n\n---\n\nTo trigger the issue, invoke omni completion for a function call to a C++ object wrapper in `std::unique_ptr`.\nThe issue does not occur when using omni completion for plain / bare pointers.\nUsing the following code example, omni completion works as expected for `foo` and `bar` but not `baz`.\n```c++\n#include <memory>\n#include <vector>\n\nint main(int argc, const char *argv[]) {\n\tstd::vector<int> foo;\n\tstd::vector<int> *bar {nullptr};\n\tstd::unique_ptr<std::vector<int>> baz;\n\n\treturn 0;\n}\n```\n\nTyping `baz->i_CTRL-X_CTRL-O` leads to `->` being deleted when the completion menu is shown.\n\nIf using LSP `autotrigger = true` this bug makes it extremely difficult to write any code using unique_ptr or similar wrapper classes.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn C++ code, omni completion should never delete the `->` (or `.`) operators.\n\nThis bug did not exist in neovim 0.11\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nApple clangd version 17.0.0 (clang-1700.6.4.2)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.7.5\n\n### Log file\n\n[lsp.log](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/26666567/lsp.log)",
